caption: This spot always delivers. They have fresh dishes for convenient rates, there is no waiting time even when the spot is packed.
Delicious, even as takeout.  Pork belly buns were A+

We came to this place for lunch. we heard about this place from a lot of people.  Well, it was very nice. The staff members welcomed us with a smile and we had a fantastic feeling. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant very much and we will visit this place again. We recommend this place to all.

I don’t need restaurant staff to be friendly but the only staff who works is a young man with a bad attitude.  The food is far beyond authentic (or tasty).  I am highly skeptical about whether the kitchen staff actually knows how to cook Korean food with ingredients that are essential for each dish.  Iceberg cabbage in bibimbap —Really?? How about yellow radish side dish with only sesame oil and few pepper flakes? I am sorry but to be truthful, I don’t remember having Korean food worse than those I ordered from this restaurant.
Easy COVID safe pickup and delicious food. Can't wait to go back in the restaurant.
amazing i come here weekly now for the wings  and kimichi fries
Very good
Awesome food, super friendly employees, always excellent character. They charge reasonable pricing and the food quality is fantastic. Kudos.
Currently having my 3rd vegetarian meal from Mokja, and each option I've tried has been completely delicious! Extremely fast service as well. This is the perfect comfort-food takeout spot.
Ordered delivery. Delivery came missing a meal. Unable to contact them to get a refund as they won't answer the phone. Very frustrating!
I am ashamed to say I never had bibimbap before coming here. However, now I just can't stop eating it, especially Mokja's! The ingredients are so fresh and great tasting.
Had a awesome experience in this spot with my friend. The food arrives quick and the customer service is just excellent. Prices are fair.

Ordered takeout at Mokja thinking it was at the UES location. Turns out I was wrong and it was ordered here. My bad on my part. I got here an hour later than pickup time but all went well. The female working there noticed I was huffing & puffing. Asked if I was ok and I told her the whole story of what happened. I just missed the pouring rain too. She was so sweet and wished me well after I picked up my order. An hour later at home, I tried the food and everything was delicious!!!  I ordered 12pc wings (half/half), spicy tuna kimbap, and kimchi pork tofu stew. I couldn't really differentiate all too much between the soy garlic wings and the gochujang(?) ones but either way, it was delicious. Even reheated in an air fryer the next day! The kimbap was standard but tasty. The kimchi stew for me was the star of the takeout. It hit the spot and fulfilled the craving for me! Although by time I got home, 1/4 of the soup was gone because the pork soaked most of it, we still were able to eat it with rice and the banchan served with the meal. We even had some leftovers for the next day, still just as good.  If am ever in the area again, I would definitely come here to get food. Solid Korean food. The prices weren't too bad either!
Yummy spare ribs. When I went they weren't staying people. It was  just pick up and delivery. Definitely worth going because their food is delicious!

I ordered online and had my food delivered. I had Rabokki and Army Stew. While Rabokki and delivery time were reasonable, Army Stew which is the main dish was disappointing and not worth what it costs at all. First of all it did not contain ramen noodles (and the menu clearly described it will have the noodles). As a person who enjoys Korean food everyday and visits Ktown very often, I expect Army Stews to have lots of meat. Instead, what I got had VERY FEW LITTLE PIECES of sausage and spam and ONLY ONE little piece of tofu! Not up to expectations at all. The price of the Army Stew was a bit on the cheaper side so, if you are not putting the ingredients it's supposed to have because of its price, just raise the price! I don't get it. Just disappointing.

Good Korean food on the UWS with great service. I have not ordered delivery but may consider it now. Very reasonable prices especially if you can't get to Jersey.  Note: I will admit it isn't the best Korean food I have had, but great option if you don't want to go all the way downtown.
